\par The fire, he now saw, had been lit in the grate. This surprised him. He stopped moving and listened intently, for a man\rquote s voice spoke within the room; it sounded timid and fearful.
\par \lquote There is a little more in the bottle, my Lord, if you are still hungry.\rquote 
\par \lquote Later,\rquote  said a second voice. This, too, belonged to a man \endash  but it was strangely high-pitched, and cold as a sudden blast of icy wind. Something about that voice made the sparse hairs on the back of Frank\rquote s neck stand up. 
