\par Frank turned his right ear towards the door, the better to hear. There came the chink of a bottle being put down upon some hard surface, and then the dull scraping noise of a heavy chair being dragged across the floor. Frank caught a glimpse of a small ma
n, his back to the door, pushing the chair into place. He was wearing a long black cloak, and there was a bald patch at the back of his head. Then he disappeared from sight again.
\par \lquote Where is Nagini?\rquote  said the cold voice.
\par \lquote I \endash  I don\rquote t know, my Lord,\rquote  said the first voice nervously. \lquote She set out to explore the house, I think ...\rquote 
\par \lquote You will milk her before we retire, Wormtail,\rquote  said the second voice. \lquote I will need feeding in the night. The journey has tired me greatly.\rquote 
\par Brow furrowed, Frank inclined his good ear still closer to the door, listening very hard. There was a pause, and then the man called Wormtail spoke again.
\par \lquote My Lord, may I ask how long we are going to stay here?\rquote 
\par \lquote A week,\rquote  said the cold voice. \lquote Perhaps longer. The place is moderately comfortable, and the plan cannot proceed yet. It would be foolish to act before the Quidditch World Cup is over.\rquote 
\par Frank inserted a gnarled finger into his ear and rotated it. Owing, no doubt, to a build-up of earwax, he had heard the word \lquote Quidditch\rquote , which was not a word at all.
\par \lquote The \endash  the Quidditch World Cup, my Lord?\rquote  said Wormtail. (Frank dug his finger still more vigorously into his ear.) \lquote Forgive me, but \endash  I do not understand \endash  why should we wait until the World Cup is over?\rquote 

\par \lquote Because, fool, at this very moment wiza
rds are pouring into the country from all over the world, and every meddler from the Ministry of Magic will be on duty, on the watch for signs of unusual activity, checking and double-checking identities. They will be obsessed with security, lest the Mugg
les notice anything. So we wait.\rquote 
\par Frank stopped trying to clear his ear out. He had distinctly heard the words \lquote Ministry of Magic\rquote , \lquote wizards\rquote  and \lquote Muggles\rquote 
. Plainly, each of these expressions meant something secret, and Frank could think of only two sorts of people who would speak in code \endash  spies and criminals. Frank tightened his hold on his walking stick once more, and listened more closely still.

\par \lquote Your Lordship is still determined, then?\rquote  Wormtail said quietly.
\par \lquote Certainly I am determined, Wormtail.\rquote  There was a note of menace in the cold voice now.
\par A slight pause followed \endash  and then Wormtail spoke, the words tumbling from him in a rush, as though he was forcing himself to say this before he lost his nerve.
\par \lquote It could be done without Harry Potter, my Lord.\rquote 
\par Another pause, more protracted, and then \endash 
\par \lquote Without Harry Potter?\rquote  breathed the second voice softly. \lquote I see ...\rquote 
