oudly, but that wasn\rquote t real\-ly an option. Instead he tried to interest himself in a beetle crawling along the stone reindeer\rquote s back, but the beetle just wasn\rquote t interesting enough to block out Hagrid\rquote s next words.
\par \lquote I jus\rquote  knew ... knew you were like me ... was it yer mother or yer father?\rquote 
\par \lquote I \endash  I don\rquote t know what you mean, \rquote Agrid ...\rquote 
