revealing his ignorance of the wizarding world. Brought up by the Dursleys, there were many things that wizards took for granted that were revelations to Harry, but these surprises had become fewer as he had moved up the school. Now, however, he could tel
l that most wizards would not have said \lquote So what?\rquote  upon finding out that one of their friends had a giantess for a mother.
