\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi284\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 
Over on the Slytherin table, Malfoy, Crabbe and Goyle were laughing at him, tapping their heads with their fingers, pulling grotesquely mad faces and waggling their tongues like snakes.
\par \lquote How did she know your scar hurt in Divination?\rquote  Ron said. \lquote There\rquote s no way she was there, there\rquote s no way she could\rquote ve heard \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote The window was open,\rquote  said Harry. \lquote I opened it to breathe.\rquote 
\par \lquote You were at the top of North Tower!\rquote  Hermione said. \lquote Your voice couldn\rquote t have carried all the way down to the grounds!\rquote 
\par \lquote Well, you\rquote re the one who\rquote s supposed to be researching magi\-cal methods of bugging!\rquote  said Harry. \lquote You tell me how she did it!\rquote 
\par \lquote I\rquote ve been trying!\rquote  said Hermione. \lquote But I ... but ...\rquote 
\par An odd, dreamy expression suddenly came over Hermione\rquote s face. She slowly raised a hand, and ran her fingers through her hair.
\par \lquote Are you all right?\rquote  said Ron, frowning at her.
\par \lquote Yes,\rquote  said Hermione breathlessly. She ran her fingers through her hair again, and then held her hand up to her mouth, as though speaking into an invisible walkie-talkie. Harry and Ron stared at each other.
\par \lquote I\rquote ve had an idea,\rquote  Hermione said, gazing into space. \lquote I think I know ... because then no one would be able to see ... even Moody ... and she\rquote d have been able to get onto the window-ledge ... but she\rquote 
s not allowed ... she\rquote s }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 definitely }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 not allowed ... I think we\rquote 
