\par Harry finished his breakfast in the emp
tying Great Hall. He saw Fleur Delacour get up from the Ravenclaw table and join Cedric as he crossed to the side chamber and entered. Krum slouched off to join them shortly afterwards. Harry stayed where he was. He really didn\rquote 
t want to go into the chamber. He had no family \endash  no family who would turn up to see him risk his life, anyway. But just as he was getting up, thinking that he might as well go up to the library and do a spot more hex revi\-
sion, the door of the side chamber opened, and Cedric stuck his head out.
\par \lquote Harry, come on, they\rquote re waiting for you!\rquote 
\par Utterly perplexed, Harry got up. The Dursleys couldn\rquote t pos\-sibly be here, could they? He walked across the Hall and opened the door into the chamber.
\par Cedric and his parents were just inside the door. Viktor Krum was over in a corner, conversing with his dark-haired mother and father in rapid Bulgarian. He had inherited his father\rquote 
s hooked nose. On the other side of the room, Fleur was jabbering away in French to her mother. Fleur\rquote s little sister, Gabrielle, was holding her mother\rquote 
s hand. She waved at Harry, who waved back. Then he saw Mrs Weasley and Bill standing in front of the fireplace, beaming at him.
\par \lquote Surprise!\rquote  Mrs Weasley said excitedly, as Harry smiled broadly, and walked over to them. \lquote Thought we\rquote d come and watch you, Harry!\rquote  She bent down and kissed him on the cheek.
\par \lquote You all right?\rquote  said Bill, grinning at Harry and shaking his hand. \lquote Charlie wanted to come, but he couldn\rquote t get time off. He said you were incredible against the Horntail.\rquote 
\par Fleur Delacour, Harry noticed, was eyeing Bill with great interest over her mother\rquote s shoulder. Harry could tell she had no objection whatsoever to long hair or earrings with fangs on them.
\par \lquote This is really nice of you,\rquote  Harry muttered to Mrs Weasley. \lquote I thought for a moment \endash  the Dursleys \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote Hmm,\rquote  said Mrs Weasley, pursing her lips. She had always refrained from criticising the Dursleys in front of Harry, but her eyes flashed every time they were mentioned.
\par \lquote It\rquote s great being back here,\rquote  said Bill, looking around the chamber (Violet, the Fat Lady\rquote s friend, winked at him from her frame). \lquote Haven\rquote 
t seen this place for five years. Is that picture of the mad knight still around? Sir Cadogan?\rquote 
\par \lquote Oh, yeah,\rquote  said Harry, who had met Sir Cadogan the previ\-ous year.
\par \lquote And the Fat Lady?\rquote  said Bill.
\par \lquote She was here in my time,\rquote  said Mrs Weasley. \lquote She gave me such a telling-off one night when I got back to the dormitory at four in the morning \endash \rquote 
