\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\sa320\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\cf1\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af39\afs56 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\fs56\cf1\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 The Parting of the Ways
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\sa320\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\cf1\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 
Dumbledore stood up. He stared down at Barty Crouch for a moment with disgust on his face. Then he raised his wand once more and ropes flew out of it, ropes which twisted them\-selves around Barty Crouch, binding him tightly.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi284\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 He turned to Professor McGonagall. \lquote 
Minerva, could I ask you to stand guard here while I take Harry upstairs?\rquote 
\par \lquote Of course,\rquote  said Professor McGonagall. She looked slightly nauseous, as though she had just watched someone being sick. However, when she drew out her wand and pointed it at Barty Crouch, her hand was quite steady.
\par \lquote Severus,\rquote  Dumbledore turned to Snape, \lquote please tell Madam Pomfrey to come down here. We need to get Alastor Moody into the hospital wing. Then go down into the grounds, find Cornelius Fudge, and bring him up to this 
office. He will undoubtedly want to question Crouch himself. Tell him I will be in the hospital wing in half an hour\rquote s time if he needs me.\rquote 
\par Snape nodded silently and swept out of the room.
\par \lquote Harry?\rquote  Dumbledore said gently.
\par Harry got up and swayed again; the pain in his leg, which he had not noticed all the time he had listened to Crouch, now returned in full measure. He also realised that he was shaking. Dumbledore gripped his arm, and helped him out into the dark corridor.

\par \lquote I want you to come up to my office first, Harry,\rquote  he said quietly, as they headed up the passageway. \lquote Sirius is waiting for us there.\rquote 
\par Harry nodded. A kind of numbness and a sense of complete unreality were upon him, but he did not care; he was even glad of it. He didn\rquote t want to have to think about anything that had happened since he had first touched the Triwizard Cup. He didn
\rquote t want to have to examine the memories, fresh and sharp as photographs, which kept flashing across his mind. Mad-Eye Moody, inside the trunk. Wormtail, slumped on 
the ground, cradling his stump of an arm. Voldemort, rising from the steaming cauldron. Cedric ... dead ... Cedric, asking to be returned to his parents ...
\par \lquote Professor,\rquote  Harry mumbled, \lquote where are Mr and Mrs Diggory?\rquote 
\par \lquote They are with Professor Sprout,\rquote  said Dumbledore. His voice, which had been so calm throughout the interrogation of Barty Crouch, shook very slightly for the first time. \lquote She was Head of Cedric\rquote s house, and knew him best.
\rquote 
\par They had reached the stone gargoyle. Dumbledore gave the password, it sprang aside, and he and Harry went up the mov\-ing spiral staircase to the oak door. Dumbledore pushed it open.
\par Sirius was standing there. His face was white and gaunt as it had been when he had escaped Azkaban. In one swift moment, he had crossed the room. \lquote Harry, are you all right? I knew it \endash  I knew something like this \endash  what happened?
\rquote 
\par His hands shook as he helped Harry into a chair in front of the desk.
\par \lquote What happened?\rquote  he asked, more urgently.
\par Dumbledore began to tell Sirius everything Barty Crouch had said. Harry was only half listening. So tired every bone in his body was aching, he wanted nothing more than to sit here, undisturbed, for hours and hours, until he fell asleep, and didn\rquote 
t have to think or feel any more.
\par There was a soft rush of wings. Fawkes the phoenix had left his perch, flown across the office, and landed on Harry\rquote s knee.
\par \lquote  \rquote Lo, Fawkes,\rquote  said Harry quietly. He stroked the phoenix\rquote s beautiful scarlet and gold plumage. Fawkes blinked peacefully up at him. There was something comforting about his warm weight.
\par Dumbledore had stopped talking. He sat down opposite Harry, behind his desk. He was looking at Harry, who avoided his eyes. Dumbledore was going to question him. He was going to make Harry relive everything.
\par \lquote I need to know what happened after you touched the Portkey in the maze, Harry,\rquote  said Dumbledore.
\par \lquote We can leave that \rquote til morning, can\rquote t we, Dumbledore?\rquote  said Sirius harshly. He had put a hand on Harry\rquote s shoulder. \lquote Let him have a sleep. Let him rest.\rquote 
\par Harry felt a rush of gratitude towards Sirius, but Dumbledore took no notice of Sirius\rquote  words. He leant forward towards Harry. Very unwillingly, Harry raised his head, and looked into those blue eyes.
\par \lquote If I thought I could help you,\rquote  Dumbledore said gently, \lquote by putting you into an enchanted sleep, and allowing you to post\-
pone the moment when you would have to think about what has happened tonight, I would do it. But I know better. Numbing the pain for a while will make it worse
 when you finally feel it. You have shown bravery beyond anything I could have expected of you. I ask you to demonstrate your courage one more time. I ask you to tell us what happened.\rquote 
\par The phoenix let out one soft, quavering note. It shivered in the air, and Harry felt as though a drop of hot liquid had slipped down his throat into his stomach, warming him, and strengthening him.
\par He took a deep breath, and began to tell them. As he spoke, visions of everything that had passed that night seemed to rise befo
re his eyes; he saw the sparkling surface of the Potion which had revived Voldemort; he saw the Death Eaters Apparating between the graves around them; he saw Cedric\rquote s body, lying on the ground beside the Cup.
\par Once or twice, Sirius made a noise as though about to say something, his hand still tight on Harry\rquote 
s shoulder, but Dumbledore raised his hand to stop him, and Harry was glad of this, because it was easier to keep going now he had started. It was even a relief; he felt almost as though something pois\-o
nous was being extracted from him; it was costing him every bit of determination he had to keep talking, yet he sensed that once he had finished, he would feel better.
\par When Harry told of Wormtail piercing his arm with the dagger, however, Sirius let out a 
vehement exclamation; and Dumbledore stood up so quickly that Harry started. Dumbledore walked around the desk and told Harry to stretch out his arm. Harry showed them both the place where his robes were torn, and the cut beneath them.
\par \lquote He said my blood would make him stronger than if he\rquote d used someone else\rquote s,\rquote  Harry told Dumbledore. \lquote He said the pro\-tection my \endash  my mother left in me \endash  he\rquote d have it, too. And he was right \endash 
 he could touch me without hurting himself, he touched my face.\rquote 
\par For a fleeting instant, Harry thought he saw a gleam of something like triumph in Dumbledore\rquote s eyes. But next sec\-
ond, Harry was sure he had imagined it, for when Dumbledore had returned to his seat behind the desk, he looked as old and weary as Harry had ever seen him.
\par \lquote Very well,\rquote  he said, sitting down again. \lquote Voldemort has over\-come that particular barrier. Harry, continue, please.\rquote 
\par Harry went on; he explained how Voldemort had emerged from the cauldron, and told them all he could remember of Voldemort\rquote s speech to the Death Eaters. Then he told how Voldemort had untied him, returned his wand to him, and pre\-pared to duel.

\par But when he reached the part where the golden beam of light had connected his and Voldemort\rquote s wands, he found his throat obstructed. He tried to keep talking, but the memories of what had come out of Voldemort\rquote 
s wand were flooding into his mind. He could see Cedric emerging, see the old man, Bertha Jorkins ... his mother ... his father ...
\par He was glad when Sirius broke the silence.
\par \lquote The wands connected?\rquote  he said, looking from Harry to Dumbledore. \lquote Why?\rquote 
\par Harry looked up again at Dumbledore, on whose face there was an arrested look.
\par \lquote Priori Incantatem,\rquote  he muttered.
\par His eyes gazed into Harry\rquote s and it was almost as though an invisible beam of understanding shot between them.
\par \lquote The reverse spell effect?\rquote  said Sirius sharply.
\par \lquote Exactly,\rquote  said Dumbledore. \lquote Harry\rquote s wand and Voldemort\rquote s wand share cores. Each of them contains a feather from the tail of the same phoenix. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af39 \ltrch\fcs0 
\i\f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 This}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133  phoenix, in fact,\rquote  he added, and he pointed at the scarlet and gold bird, perching peacefully on Harry
\rquote s knee.
\par \lquote My wand\rquote s feather came from Fawkes?\rquote  Harry said, amazed.
\par \lquote Yes,\rquote  said Dumbledore. \lquote Mr Ollivander wrote to tell me you had bought the second wand, the moment you left his shop four years ago.\rquote 
\par \lquote So what happens when a wand meets its brother?\rquote  said Sirius.
\par \lquote They will not work properly against each other,\rquote  said Dumbledore. \lquote If, however, the owners of the wands force the wands to do battle ... a very rare effect will take place.
\par \lquote One of the wands will force the other to regurgitate spells it has performed \endash  in reverse. The most recent first ... and then those which preceded it ...\rquote 
\par He looked interrogatively at Harry, and Harry nodded.
\par \lquote Which means,\rquote  said Dumbledore slowly, his eyes upon Harry\rquote s face, \lquote that some form of Cedric must have reappeared.\rquote 
\par Harry nodded again.
\par \lquote Diggory came back to life?\rquote  said Sirius sharply.
\par \lquote No spell can reawaken the dead,\rquote  said Dumbledore heavily. \lquote All that would have happened is a kind of reverse echo. A shadow of the living Cedric would have emerged from the wand ... am I correct, Harry?\rquote 
\par \lquote He spoke to me,\rquote  Harry said. He was suddenly shaking again. The ... the ghost Cedric, or whatever he was, spoke.\rquote 
\par \lquote An echo,\rquote  said Dumbledore, \lquote which retained Cedric\rquote s appear\-ance and character. I am guessing other such forms appeared ... less recent victims of Voldemort\rquote s wand ...\rquote 
\par \lquote An old man,\rquote  Harry said, his throat still constricted. \lquote Bertha Jorkins. And ...\rquote 
\par \lquote Your parents?\rquote  said Dumbledore quietly.
\par \lquote Yes,\rquote  said Harry.
\par Sirius\rquote  grip on Harry\rquote s shoulder was now so tight it was painful.
\par \lquote The last murders the wand performed,\rquote  said Dumbledore, nodding. \lquote In reverse order. More would have appeared, of course, had you maintained the connection. Very well, Harry, these echoes, these shadows ... what did they do?\rquote 

\par Harry described how the figures which had emerged from the wand had prowled the edges of the golden web, how Voldemort had seemed to fear them, how the shadow of Harry\rquote s father had told him what to do, how Cedric\rquote s had 
made its final request.
\par At this point, Harry found he could not continue. He looked around at Sirius, and saw that he had his face in his hands.
\par Harry suddenly became aware that Fawkes had left his knee. The phoenix had fluttered to the floor. It was resting its beauti\-ful head against Harry\rquote 
s injured leg, and thick, pearly tears were falling from its eyes onto the wound left by the spider. The pain vanished. The skin mended. His leg was repaired.
\par \lquote I will say it again,\rquote  said Dumbledore, as the phoenix rose into the air, and resettled itself upon the perch beside the door. \lquote You have shown bravery beyond anything I could have expect\-
ed of you tonight, Harry. You have shown bravery equal to those who died fighting Voldemort at the height of his powers. You have shouldered a grown wizard\rquote s burden and found your\-self equal to it \endash 
 and you have now given us all that we have a right to expect. You will come with me to the hospital wing. I do not want you returning to the dormitory tonight. A Sleeping Potion, and some peace ... Sirius, would you like to stay with him?\rquote 
\par Sirius nodded, and stood up. He transformed back into the great black dog, and walked with Harry and Dumbledore out of the office, accompanying them down a flight of stairs to the hospital wing.
\par When Dumbledore pushed open the door, Harry saw Mrs Weasley, Bill, Ron and Hermione grouped around a harassed-looking Madam Pomfrey. They appeared to be demanding to know where Harry was and what had happened to him.
\par All of them whipped around as Harry, Dumbledore and the black dog entered, and Mrs Weasley let out a kind of muffled scream. \lquote Harry! Oh, Harry!\rquote 
\par She started to hurry towards him, but Dumbledore moved between them.
\par \lquote Molly,\rquote  he said, holding up a hand, \lquote please listen to me for a moment. Harry has been t
hrough a terrible ordeal tonight. He has just had to relive it for me. What he needs now is sleep, and peace, and quiet. If he would like you all to stay with him,\rquote  he added, looking around at Ron, Hermione and Bill, too, \lquote 
you may do so. But I do not want you questioning him until he is ready to answer, and certainly not this evening.\rquote 
\par Mrs Weasley nodded. She was very white.
\par She rounded on Ron, Hermione and Bill as though they were being noisy, and hissed, \lquote Did you hear? He needs quiet!\rquote 
\par \lquote Headmaster,\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey, staring at the great black dog that was Sirius, \lquote may I ask what \endash ?\rquote 
\par \lquote This dog will be remaining with Harry for a while,\rquote  said Dumbledore simply. \lquote I assure you, he is extremely well trained. Harry \endash  I will wait while you get into bed.\rquote 
\par Harry felt an inexpressible sense of gratitude to Dumbledore for asking the others not to question him. It wasn\rquote t as though he didn\rquote 
t want them there; but the thought of explaining it all over again, the idea of reliving it one more time, was more than he could stand.
\par \lquote I will be back to see you as soon as I have met with Fudge, Harry,\rquote  said Dumbledore. \lquote I would like you to remain here tomorrow, until I have spoken to the school.\rquote  He left.
\par As Madam Pomfrey led Harry to a nearby bed, he caught sight of the real Moody lying motionless in a bed at the far end of the room. His wooden leg and magical eye were lying on the bedside table.
\par \lquote Is he OK?\rquote  Harry asked.
\par \lquote He\rquote ll be fine,\rquote  said Madam Pomfrey, giving Harry some pyja\-mas and pulling screens around him. He took 
off his robes, pulled on the pyjamas and got into bed. Ron, Hermione, Bill, Mrs Weasley and the black dog came around the screen and settled themselves in chairs on either side of him. Ron and Hermione were looking at him almost cautiously, as though scar
ed of him.
\par \lquote I\rquote m all right,\rquote  he told them. \lquote Just tired.\rquote 
\par Mrs Weasley\rquote s eyes filled with tears as she smoothed his bed\-covers unnecessarily.
\par Madam Pomfrey, who had bustled off to her office, returned holding a goblet and a small bottle of some purple potion.
\par \lquote You\rquote ll need to drink all of this, Harry,\rquote  she said. \lquote It\rquote s a potion for dreamless sleep.\rquote 
\par Harry took the goblet and drank a few mouthfuls. He felt himself becoming drowsy at once. Everything around him became hazy; the lamps around the hospital wing seemed
 to be winking at him in a friendly way through the screen around his bed; his body felt as though it was sinking deeper into the warmth of the feather mattress. Before he could finish the Potion, before he could say another word, his exhaustion had carri
ed him off to sleep.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qc \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 *
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 Harry woke up, so warm, so very sleepy, that he didn\rquote 
t open his eyes, wanting to drop off again. The room was still dimly lit; he was sure it was still night-time, and had a feeling that he couldn\rquote t have been asleep very long.
\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi284\li0\ri0\nowidctlpar\wrapdefault\faauto\rin0\lin0\itap0 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 Then he heard whispering around him.
\par \lquote They\rquote ll wake him if they don\rquote t shut up!\rquote 
\par \lquote What are they shouting about? Nothing else can have hap\-pened, can it?\rquote 
\par Harry opened his eyes blearily. Someone had removed his glasses. He could see the fuzzy outlines of Mrs Weasley and Bill close by. Mrs Weasley was on her feet.
\par \lquote That\rquote s Fudge\rquote s voice,\rquote  she whispered. \lquote And that\rquote s Minerva McGonagall\rquote s, isn\rquote t it? But what are they arguing about?\rquote 
\par Now Harry could hear them, too: people shouting and run\-ning towards the hospital wing.
\par \lquote Regrettable, but all the same, Minerva \endash \rquote  Cornelius Fudge was saying loudly.
\par \lquote You should never have brought it inside the castle!\rquote  yelled Professor McGonagall. \lquote When Dumbledore finds out \endash \rquote 
\par Harry heard hospital doors burst open. Unnoticed by any of the people around his bed, all of whom were staring at the door as Bill pulled back the screens, Harry sat up, and put his glasses back on.
\par Fudge came striding up the ward. Professors McGonagall and Snape were at his heels.
\par \lquote Where\rquote s Dumbledore?\rquote  Fudge demanded of Mrs Weasley.
\par \lquote He\rquote s not here,\rquote  said Mrs Weasley angrily. \lquote This is a hospital wing, Minister, don\rquote t you think you\rquote d do better to \endash \rquote 
\par But the door opened, and Dumbledore came sweeping up the ward.
\par \lquote What has happened?\rquote  said Dumbledore sharply, looking from Fudge to Professor McGonagall. \lquote Why are you disturbing these people? Minerva, I\rquote m surprised at you \endash  I asked you to stand guard over Barty Crouch \endash 
\rquote 
\par \lquote There is no need to stand guard over him any more, Dumbledore!\rquote  she shrieked. \lquote The Minister has seen to that!\rquote 
\par Harry had never seen Professor McGonagall lose control like this. There were angry blotches of colour in her cheeks, her hands were balled into fists; she was trembling with fury.
\par \lquote When we told Mr Fudge that we had caught the Death Eater responsible for tonight\rquote s events,\rquote  said Snape, in a low voice, \lquote 
he seemed to feel his personal safety was in question. He insisted on summoning a Dementor to accompany him into the castle. He brought it up to the office where Barty Crouch \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote I told him you would not agree, Dumbledore!\rquote  stormed Professor McGonagall. \lquote I told him you would never allow Dementors to set foot inside the castle, but \endash \rquote 
\par \lquote My dear woman!\rquote  roared Fudge, who likewise looked angri\-er than Harry had ever seen him. \lquote As Minister for Magic, it is my decision whether I wish to bring protection with me when interviewing a possibly dangerous \endash \rquote 

\par But Professor McGonagall\rquote s voice drowned Fudge\rquote s.
\par \lquote The moment that \endash  that thing entered the room,\rquote  she screamed, pointing at Fudge, trembling all over, \lquote it swooped down on Crouch and \endash  and \endash \rquote 
\par Harry felt a chill in his stomach, as Professor McGonagall struggled to find words to describe what had happened. He did not need her to finish her sentence. He knew what the Dementor must 
have done. It had administered its fatal kiss to Barty Crouch. It had sucked his soul out through his mouth. He was worse than dead.
\par \lquote By all accounts, he is no loss!\rquote  blustered Fudge. \lquote It seems he has been responsible for several deaths!\rquote 
\par \lquote But he cannot now give testimony, Cornelius,\rquote  said Dumbledore. He was staring hard at Fudge, as though seeing him plainly for the first time. \lquote He cannot give evidence about why he killed those people.\rquote 
\par \lquote Why he killed them? Well, that\rquote s no mystery, is it?\rquote  blustered Fudge. \lquote He was a raving lunatic! From what Minerva and Severus have told me, he seems to have thought he was doing it all on You-Know-Who\rquote s instructions!
\rquote 
\par \lquote Lord Voldemort }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ai\af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \i\f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af39 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\lang2057\langfe3081\langnp2057\insrsid15346133  giving him instructions, Cornelius,\rquote 
 Dumbledore said. \lquote Those people\rquote s deaths were mere by-products of a plan to restore Voldemort to full strength again. The plan succeeded. Voldemort has been restored to his body.\rquote 
\par Fudge looked as though someone had just swung a heavy weight into his face. Dazed and blinking, he stared back at Dumbledore as if he couldn\rquote t quite believe what he had just heard.
\par He began to splutter, still goggling at Dumbledore. \lquote You-Know-Who ... returned? Preposterous. Come now, Dumbledore ...\rquote 
