ly figure, a little blustering, a little pompous, but essentially good-natured. But now a short, angry wizard stood before him, refusing, point-blank, to accept the prospect of disruption in his comfortable and ordered world \endash 
 to believe that Voldemort could have risen.
\par \lquote Voldemort has returned,\rquote  Dumbledore repeated. \lquote 
If you accept that fact straight away, Fudge, and take the necessary measures, we may still be able to save the situation. The first and most essential step is to remove Azkaban from the control of the Dementors \endash \rquote 
