\par Mrs Weasley screamed and leapt back from the bed.
\par \lquote Sirius Black!\rquote  she shrieked, pointing at him.
\par \lquote Mum, shut up!\rquote  Ron yelled. \lquote It\rquote s OK!\rquote 
\par Snape had not yelled or jumped backwards, but the look on his face was one of mingled fury and horror.
\par \lquote Him!\rquote  he snarled, staring at Sirius, whose face showed equal dislike. \lquote What is he doing here?\rquote 
\par \lquote He is here at my invitation,\rquote  said Dumbledore, looking between them, \lquote as are you, Severus. I trust you both. It is time for you to lay aside your old differences, and trust each other.\rquote 
\par Harry thought Dumbledore was asking for a near miracle. Sirius and Snape were eyeing each other with the utmost loathing.
\par \lquote I will settle, in the short term,\rquote  said Dumbledore, with a bite of impatience in his voice, \lquote for a lack of open 
hostility. You will shake hands. You are on the same side now. Time is short, and unless the few of us who know the truth stand united, there is no hope for any of us.\rquote 
\par Very slowly \endash  but still glaring at each other as though each wished the other nothing but ill \endash  Sirius and Snape moved towards each other, and shook hands. They let go extremely quickly.
\par \lquote That will do to be going on with,\rquote  said Dumbledore, step\-ping between them once more. \lquote Now I have work for each of you. Fudge\rquote s attitude, though not unexpe
cted, changes everything. Sirius, I need you to set off at once. You are to alert Remus Lupin, Arabella Figg, Mundungus Fletcher \endash  the old crowd. Lie low at Lupin\rquote s for a while, I will contact you there.\rquote 
\par \lquote But \endash \rquote  said Harry.
\par He wanted Sirius to stay. He did not want to say goodbye again so quickly.
\par \lquote You\rquote ll see me very soon, Harry,\rquote  said Sirius, turning to him. \lquote I promise you. But I must do what I can, you understand, don\rquote t you?\rquote 
\par \lquote Yeah,\rquote  said Harry. \lquote Yeah ... of course I do.\rquote 
\par Sirius grasped his hand briefly, nodded to Dumbledore, trans\-formed again into the black dog, and ran the length of the room to the door, whose handle he turned with a paw. Then he was gone.
\par \lquote Severus,\rquote  said Dumbledore, turning to Snape, \lquote you know what I must ask you to do. If you are ready ... if you are pre\-pared ...\rquote 
\par \lquote I am,\rquote  said Snape.
\par He looked slightly paler than usual, and his cold, black eyes glittered strangely.
\par \lquote Then, good luck,\rquote  said Dumbledore, and he watched, with a trace of apprehension on his face, as Snape swept wordlessly after Sirius.
\par It was several minutes before Dumbledore spoke again.
\par \lquote I must go downstairs,\rquote  he said finally. \lquote I must see the Diggorys. Harry \endash  take the rest of your potion. I will see all of you later.\rquote 
\par Harry slumped back against his pillows as Dumbledore dis\-appeared. Hermione, Ron and Mrs Weasley were all looking at him. None of them spoke for a very long time.
