\par \lquote It wasn\rquote t your fault, Harry,\rquote  Mrs Weasley whispered.
\par \lquote I told him to take the Cup with me,\rquote  said Harry.
\par Now the burning feeling was in his throat, too. He wished Ron would look away.
\par Mrs Weasley 
set the potion down on the bedside cabinet, bent down, and put her arms around Harry. He had no memory of ever being hugged like this, as though by a mother. The full weight of everything he had seen that night seemed to fall in upon him as Mrs Weasley he
ld him to her. His mother\rquote s face, his father\rquote 
s voice, the sight of Cedric, dead on the ground, all started spinning in his head until he could hardly bear it, until he was screwing up his face against the howl of misery fighting to get out of him.
